comments.body:
**Root cause identified and fixed.**

The `outlookSearchEmails` handler (now `outlook_search_emails`) was wrapping the KQL query in double-quotes before encoding:

```typescript
// BUGGY (before):
$search=${encodeURIComponent(`"${query}"`)}
// О“ГҘГҶ Graph receives: $search=%22from%3Auser%40domain.com%22
// О“ГҘГҶ Interpreted as phrase search in message body О“ГҮГ¶ always 0 results for sender queries

// FIXED:
$search=${encodeURIComponent(query)}
// О“ГҘГҶ Graph receives: $search=from%3Auser%40domain.com
// О“ГҘГҶ Interpreted as KQL property filter О“ГҮГ¶ correctly filters by sender
```

The double-quote wrapper converted any KQL property filter (`from:`, `subject:`, `hasAttachment:`) into a literal phrase match against the message body. A query like `from:eric@eanderson.de` was searching for the string `"from:eric@eanderson.de"` in the email body text rather than filtering by sender.

Also added an empty-result diagnostic: if 0 messages match, the tool returns a `diagnostic` field explaining the query scope and suggesting KQL syntax examples.

**Commit:** `6a5132c` О“ГҮГ¶ pushed to main, deployment in progress via `deploy-stamp.yml`.

Issues #305, #306, #308, #309, #310, #311 are all duplicates of this root cause.
